{
  "name": "leios_retry_after_bad_body",
  "description": "An EB is offered and accumulates 100 votes (quorum). The first fetch response delivers an INCORRECT body (0xff, invalid CBOR) whose blake2b-256 does not match the announced point hash. A second fetch response from the same connection delivers the CORRECT body (0xa0, empty CBOR map) whose hash does match. A conforming node must reject the first body, then accept the second, demonstrating that hash-validation failure on one fetch attempt does not permanently blacklist the EB or prevent re-validation from a subsequent response.",
